  <div class="container">
    <div class="secure-systems-header">
      <h2>Building Secure Systems</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="secure-cards-grid">
      <div class="secure-card">
        <h3>Enabling Safe Innovation</h3>
        <p>Strong security and privacy foundations support confident experimentation with autonomous agents while maintaining safety and trust.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="secure-card">
        <h3>Scaling Systems Responsibly</h3>
        <p>Adaptive protections keep pace with growing agent capabilities and increasingly complex environments.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="secure-card">
        <h3>Strengthening Trust</h3>
        <p>Clear safeguards and transparent data boundaries build confidence among users, developers, and stakeholders.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="secure-card">
        <h3>Supporting Global Interoperability</h3>
        <p>Unified, flexible frameworks help agent systems operate consistently across diverse regulatory and cultural contexts.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="key-questions">
      <h3>Key Questions</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>How do we design security systems that adapt as agents become more autonomous and capable?</li>
        <li>What privacy guarantees can we provide when agents require rich contextual information to function effectively?</li>
        <li>What privacy guarantees can we provide when agents require rich contextual information to function effectively?</li>
        <li>How do traditional security models need to evolve for systems that reason, plan, and act independently?</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Research Approach -->
<div class="research-approach-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="research-approach-header">
      <h2>Research Approach</h2>
      <p>We take an evidence-driven approach to understanding how security controls, privacy models, and governance frameworks must evolve for agentic architectures. Our work spans exploratory prototyping, adversarial testing, and collaborative design.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="research-item">
      <div class="research-item-text">
        <h3>Adaptive Security for Autonomous Agents</h3>
        <p>The traditional security model of "trust but verify" doesn't hold when agents can self-modify, share tools, interact with external APIs, and execute multi-step workflows.</p>
        <p><strong>Approach:</strong> We prototype context-aware security controls that adjust based on agent behavior, interaction history, and environmental risk signals.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Agent sandboxing and capability boundaries</li>
          <li>Dynamic permission escalation with human-in-the-loop gates</li>
          <li>Behavior anomaly detection across agent interactions</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="research-item-image">
        <img src="/images/research/security-privacy/adaptive-security.png" alt="Adaptive Security for Autonomous Agents">
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="research-item reversed">
      <div class="research-item-image">
        <img src="/images/research/security-privacy/privacy-context.png" alt="Privacy-Preserving Context for Intelligent Agents">
      </div>
      <div class="research-item-text">
        <h3>Privacy-Preserving Context for Intelligent Agents</h3>
        <p>Agent AI systems must remember in order to be useful—but that memory needs to be bounded, secure, and privacy-respecting.</p>
        <p><strong>Approach:</strong> We explore memory architectures that give agents enough context to be helpful while enforcing data minimization, consent boundaries, and regulatory compliance.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Contextual memory with automatic expiration and redaction</li>
          <li>Differential privacy for agent learning signals</li>
          <li>User-controlled data scoping and consent management</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Use Cases -->
    <div class="use-cases">
      <p class="use-cases-label">Use Cases</p>
      <div class="use-cases-grid">
        <div class="use-case-card">
          <h4>Self Automation of Routine Tasks</h4>
          <p>Agents autonomously handle repetitive workflows while maintaining secure access boundaries and audit trails.</p>
          <div class="use-case-tags">
            <span class="use-case-tag">Automation</span>
            <span class="use-case-tag">Security</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="use-case-card">
          <h4>Risk Analysis &amp; Agentic Decisions</h4>
          <p>Multi-agent systems that assess risk factors collaboratively while preserving data isolation between organizational boundaries.</p>
          <div class="use-case-tags">
            <span class="use-case-tag">Risk</span>
            <span class="use-case-tag">Multi-Agent</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="use-case-card">
          <h4>Adaptive Risk Detection</h4>
          <p>Agents that evolve their threat detection capabilities over time using privacy-preserving learning techniques.</p>
          <div class="use-case-tags">
            <span class="use-case-tag">Detection</span>
            <span class="use-case-tag">Privacy</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

